9-inch
pan.
Bake
15 minutes. Add walnuts to reserved crumb mixture.
In heavy saucepan over low heat,
melt caramels
with sweetened condensed milk, stirring until
smooth. Spoon
apple filling over prepared crust.
Top with
caramel mixture,
then reserved crumb mixture.
Bake 20 minutes or until set.
Cool; serve warm with ice cream.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour until it looks like coarse corn meal.
Blend egg in a cup.
Add the water and vinegar to the eggs. Blend well and add to mixture.
Add salt and blend until it holds together well.
Flour board lightly and roll out dough to fit pan. Makes 3 crusts.

title: st. paul's rice
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Saute onions with celery sticks in a small amount of butter.
Combine soup in boiling water and cook for 7 minutes.
Add rice to soup mixture, then add sausage and vegetables.
Place in casserole and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: elfo's spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Set aside. Heat 1/2 cup butter.
Add minced garlic, shrimp and chopped mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes in butter.
Add spaghetti to skillet and sprinkle with Romano cheese, salt, pepper and monosodium glutamate.
Using large spoon, stir spaghetti being careful not to cut it.
Continue until heated and be careful not to let butter brown.

title: best salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Chill before using.

title: green beans and tomatoes
directions: Cut beans lengthwise.
Chop onions.
Combine all ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Cook, covered, for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli-cheese bake
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain and put into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine soup with milk, stirring until smooth.
Pour half of soup mixture over broccoli.
Sprinkle grated cheese over soup layer; add remaining soup.
Top with buttered bread cubes; bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Yield:
6 servings.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: *Stew chicken. Strain and save broth.
Remove skin and bones and break meat into pieces.
Place on bottom of a 9 x 12-inch greased glass pan.
Saute mushrooms in a little of the broth.
Mix mushrooms, soup and sour cream together.
Place on top of chicken. Mix stuffing with 1/2 pound melted butter or margarine and 1 cup broth.
Place on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until dressing is browned.

title: taloren
directions: Brown beef in 2 tablespoons cooking oil.
Salt to taste.
Cook until tender.
Add celery, peppers and onions.
Combine all ingredients, except cheese, in a large bowl.
Mix lightly.
Put in casserole and bake until tender.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Spray small casserole with Pam.
Add sliced eggplant, mushrooms and 1/3 cup grated cheese, mixed together.
Sprinkle basil over ingredients or other herbs and spices to suit your taste.
Cover with spaghetti sauce (add more basil, if desired). Add remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: mexicali roll-ups
directions: Spoon 1/4 of dip over each tortilla, spreading to edges. Sprinkle each with 1/4 of chicken.
Roll up.
Place seam side down on a plate or flat dish.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Cut each roll into six 1-inch pieces.
Serve with salsa.
Makes 24 appetizers.

title: breakfast scones
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt, then cut in butter to make crumbles.
Add dried fruit, ginger and lemon peel, mixing well.
Add buttermilk.
On a lightly floured board, knead dough 6 turns, then place on greased baking pan (12 x 15-inch) and shape into an oval loaf.
Using a floured knife, cut across loaf in triangles to form pie shaped slices.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until top is brown.

title: raspberry peach parfait
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in boiling water. Stir in ice cubes until dissolved.
Reserve 3/4 cup dissolved gelatin. Divide among and pour remaining gelatin evenly into 6 dessert glasses.
Chill.

title: moist cornbread
directions: Melt butter.
Blend together sugar and eggs; add butter.
Stir in buttermilk, soda, cornmeal, flour and salt.
Bake in a 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry chiffon pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Chill until partially set. Beat until fluffy.
Fold in berries.
Gradually beat sugar into egg whites; beat until mixture stands in peaks and sugar is dissolved.
Fold egg whites and whipped cream into gelatin mixture.
Pour into cooled baked pastry shell.
Chill until set. Top with whipped cream.
Garnish with sliced strawberries.
Makes 6 servings.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and 1/2 stick margarine (melted); mix well. Add well beaten eggs; mix well.
Add milk and flavoring; mix well. Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Dot with remaining margarine. Sprinkle with nutmeg, if desired.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: busy day fruit cobbler(a juicy cobbler, southern style)
directions: Place
fruit
in
greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
(If fruit is very juicy, mix 1 tablespoon cornstarch with each cup juice.) Cream shortening
and
sugar.
Mix in egg.
Add flour and milk alternately;
mix until smooth after each addition.
Pour over fruit in pan.
Bake in 375° oven for about 30 minutes.
Cut in squares.
Serve warm with cream or whipped cream, if desired.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.
Cover with 1 cup bread crumbs.

title: okra pickles
directions: Wash okra.
Leave small amount of stem on okra.
Pack into sterilized pint jars, standing on end to get as many okra pods in jars as possible.
For hot pickles, add 1 pod of hot pepper to each jar.
For dill pickles, add sprig of dill weed to each jar. Boil vinegar; add 1/4 cup to each jar.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt to each jar.
Finish filling jar with boiling water.
Seal jars while hot.
Ready to eat in about 2 weeks.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry and brown bacon, onions and green pepper in a deep skillet.
Drain off all grease except 1 teaspoon.
Combine all other ingredients, mixing well.
Cover and cook until rice is tender and thick.

title: tortillas(for tacos)
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Work in shortening until fine and crumbly.
Add water.
Mix well with hands and knead until soft and smooth.
Divide into 8 or 12 parts.
Roll into round shape, very thin.
Bake on hot, ungreased griddle, turning until both sides are brown.
Keep warm in 150° oven.
(Be sure not to overcook, browning doesn't take long.)

title: country fair egg bread
directions: Heat 2 c. water and 1 c. milk.
Soften yeast in warm water; let set.
Combine sugar, oil and salt in large bowl; add hot milk; then add cold water.
Add eggs that have been whipped a little. Add yeast and mix.
Add between 7 and 9 c. flour, until a stiff batter.
Spread a large quantity of flour and pour out batter. Knead dough for about 7 minutes. Put into a greased bowl and let rise until doubled.
Punch down and turn over.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Turn out and shape into rolls or loaves and let rise double.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.
Brush with butter.

title: pecan bars
directions: Fill bottom of a big cookie sheet with graham cracker squares. Melt brown sugar, oleo with pecans in saucepan until it comes to a full boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir until boiling stops, then pour over crackers and spread evenly.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Take out, let cool a little and pour on wax paper.

title: zucchini-carrot casserole
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat; add zucchini, carrots and onion.
Saut 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat; stir in sour cream and next 3 ingredients.
Spoon into a lightly greased 1-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yield:
4 servings.
Prep:
15 minutes.

title: lemon beef
directions: Heat butter in large pan and saute the meat until it becomes light brown on all sides.
Add the salt, pepper, carrots, celery, parsley and the water or beef sauce and then lemon juice.
Boil it for 2 hours.
Let the meat cool and cut it in pieces.
Put the pieces in the pan again and warm the pieces for awhile.
Pour the gravy through the colander.
Make the gravy thicker by adding 2 teaspoons of flour.
Serve the meat with rice or sauteed mushrooms.

title: squash pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Peel and seed squash. Dice into pieces. Cook in saltwater until soft and tender. Drain off water.

Pure squash or beat with mixer. Mix flour and sugar together. Add to mixture. Beat on low speed. Add eggs, milks and vanilla; mix well. Pour into unbaked pie shells. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.

title: hot brandied fruit
directions: Drain fruit.
Reserve juices.
Combine juices and stir well. Set aside 1/2 cup juices.
Combine butter and sugar.
Stir until smooth.
Add reserved juice, brandy and spices.
Stir until blended.
Combine fruit in 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Pour brandy mixture in.
Microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Stir twice.

title: whole fruit shake
directions: Combine all in a blender.
Whir until blended.
Pour in tall glass.
You can also put in a handful of ice cubes.

title: cocoa-pink cuplets
directions: Sift flour, cocoa and salt together; set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening together.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add soda to cold water; stir well.
Add alternately with dry ingredients to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Blend thoroughly after each addition.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat 2 eggs slightly and pour into a well of flour mixture (flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon).
Add oil, apples, nuts and vanilla.
Mix.
Pour batter into a 15 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch greased pan.
(I use lasagna size foil pans.)
Sprinkle topping on cake.
Put in cold oven.
Set oven at 325° and bake for 50 minutes.

title: delectable date drop cookies
directions: Combine dates and water; bring to boiling.
Simmer 5 minutes. Cool. Set aside 2 tablespoons of date mixture for frosting.
Beat in egg, sugar, butter and milk.
Stir together flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: spicy meat loaf
directions: Mix together the ingredients.
Form loaf in pan (catsup on top).
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: christmas cauliflower
directions: In a large saucepan cook cauliflower in a a small amount of water for 6 to 7 minutes until crisp and tender. Drain well. In a medium saucepan saute bell peppers and mushrooms in butter for 2 minutes. Add flour and gradually stir in milk. Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and stir in cheese until melted. Add pimentos and salt. Place half of the cauliflower in a greased 2 quart
baking dish. Top with half of sauce. Repeat layers. Bake uncovered at 325 degrees for 25 minutes or until bubbly. Sprinkle with paprika if desired.

title: rum slush
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Freeze 6 to 8 hours.
Place a scoop of slush into a glass of ginger ale.
Great for parties!

title: rainbow delight cake
directions: Beat whipping cream and confectioners sugar until stiff.
To 2 cups of frosting stir in several drops of yellow food coloring and 1/2 teaspoon almond extract.
To 1 cup of frosting, add red food coloring and 1/2 teaspoon rum extract to make pink.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour in pie crust and chill for 1 hour.

title: monkey bread #1
directions: Mix white sugar and cinnamon.
Quarter biscuits with child's scissors.
Toss quarters into the cinnamon sugar mixture.
Put into greased Bundt pan; save extra sugar mixture.
Bring brown sugar and butter to boil.
A grown-up should help with this.
Pour over the biscuits and dump the rest of the sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Invert onto plate; don't let cool in pan!

title: corned beef mold
directions: Stir until dissolved.
Add and stir into first mixture.
Pour into Tupperware ring or 2 small bowls and let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown first 4 ingredients in skillet; place in crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients to crock-pot.
Stir and cook 2 hours on low. May add hot pepper to taste.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Fry the onion in oil.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute onions in oleo.
Mix all ingredients together and sprinkle 1/2 cup corn chips on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot puff
directions: Grease an 8-inch square baking dish.
Steam or boil carrots until tender (about 20 minutes).
Place margarine, eggs, sugar, flour, baking powder and vanilla in blender.
Add carrots a little at a time and puree the mixture.
Pour into greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: chinese chews
directions: Mix. Bake at 350° in 9 x 9-inch pan for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool slightly.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Make rice according to package.
When done mix in ground beef, egg and seasonings.
Arrange peppers in baking dish.
Fill each with ground beef mixture.

title: onion biscuits
directions: Add onion to butter; let stand a few minutes.
Place biscuits on ungreased baking sheet.
Press a hollow in center of each biscuit with floured bottom of small glass.
Fill hollows with butter mixture.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until done.

title: three bean and corn bread casserole
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix all ingredients except Corn Bread Topping; pour into ungreased baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inch. Prepare Corn Bread Topping; spoon evenly over bean mixture to within 1 inch of edges.
Bake until topping is deep golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the margarine, shortening and sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Combine flour, soda, salt and oatmeal.
Add to sugar mixture.
Stir in chips.
Chill dough before baking.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: country-style pot roast
directions: In Dutch oven brown roast in shortening.
Combine onion soup mix with 2 cups of water.
Pour over roast; simmer, turning occasionally for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender.
Or after browning, put into crock-pot until almost tender, then add potatoes and carrots.
Blend flour and water.
Stir into drippings where roast was browned and make gravy.
Serves 6.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine in bowl the first 3 ingredients and let stand until the moisture is taken up.
Add 1 egg and beat well.
Sift remaining ingredients and add.
Stir until combined.
Grease muffin tins and fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before removing.
Yields 12 to 15 (2 1/2-inch) muffins.

title: kraut dumplins
directions: Let come to boiling until kraut is tender.
Then drop in dumplings.
Cook until dumplings are done.
Add pepper, if
wanted (black or red pepper).

title: b & b chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken.
Remove from bones and chop.
Mix well all ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Cover with another cup of Ritz crackers (crushed).
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: power packed smoothie
directions: Puree strawberries.
Add milk, banana, instant breakfast and frozen yogurt and blend until smooth.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain cans of fruit.
Combine fruit cocktail, pineapple, apple, marshmallows and nuts in a serving bowl.
Whip whipping cream until thick, add sugar, salt and mayonnaise and mix. Add to fruit bowl and mix.
Add bananas last just before serving.

title: caesar salad
directions: Mix and toss with lettuce.

title: pork and noodles
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Cut pork into thin strips.
(Throw in the bones, too.)
Heat 2 large skillets.
Put 1 tablespoon butter into 1 skillet and add the meat.
Brown slightly.
Add the onions. Add the beans.
Cover and cook until the beans are done.
In second skillet, melt the rest of the butter until hot.
Add the cooked noodles.
Cook until crisp and brown.
Turn over and brown other side.
When noodles and meat are ready, remove half the noodles to a bowl.
Take half the meat and add it to the noodles in the pan. Put the noodles from the bowl into the other pan with the meat. Mix each pan to combine.
You now have 2 pans of stuff.
Enough to feed a crowd.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix egg yolks, margarine and milk together.
Mix sugar and flour together.
Add the two mixtures together in medium saucepan. Cook until thickened.
Coconut is optional.
Pour into 2 baked pie crusts or 1 deep-dish baked crust.

title: cashew coconut brittle
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients into 3-quart pan.
Cook over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Add cashews and coconut. Increase heat to high.
Stir constantly until mixture becomes light brown.
Remove from heat.

title: oyster stuffing
directions: Cook 4 cups celery, diced fine in 2 cups water until tender, about 18 minutes; drain and save 1 cup liquid.
Saute 1/2 cup minced onions in 1/2 cup butter over low heat.
Drain 1 1/2 cups oysters.
Add enough celery liquid to oyster liquid to make one cup.
Mix well 4 quarts lightly packed, day old bread crumbs with 2 teaspoons poultry seasoning, 1 tablespoon salt and pepper.
Then combine dry ingredients with liquid onions and oysters; blend well.

title: sylvia's cheese spread
directions: Put cheese in double boiler.
Melt and add rest of the ingredients.
Pour into containers and serve.

title: cold potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until done.
Refrigerate until cold.
When cold, peel and dice in small squares.
Dice boiled eggs.

title: sinfully delicious
directions: Mix Lorna Doone cookie crumbs with melted butter.
Press crust into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding and milk until thick. Blend softened ice cream.
Pour on crust.
Chill until firm.
Before serving, spread Cool Whip and sprinkle with crushed Heath bars.

title: mushroom saute
directions: Slice large mushrooms and leave small ones whole.
Cut onion in half, then into long, thin strips.
Melt butter with soy sauce. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until onion is almost clear.

title: frozen punch
directions: Put Jell-O in bowl.
(Jell-O should be whatever color you want punch.)
Add sugar and 4 cups of boiling water.
Dissolve Jell-O and sugar.
Add remaining 5 cups of water and pineapple juice, then freeze.
Set out of freezer 4 to 5 hours before time to serve.
At time to serve, add room temperature Sprite.
Punch should be slushy.

title: baked hash browns
directions: Place hash browns on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soups and sour cream and pour over hash browns.
Cover top with French fried onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut buddy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl beat peanut butter and butter until smooth.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Blend in flour and salt.
Stir in one cup chocolate morsels.
Spread in ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until edges begin to brown.
Sprinkle remaining chocolate over cookie layer.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spread evenly over top.
Cool completely.
Cut in 1 1/2-inch bars.
Makes about 48 bars.

title: bug spray for vegetable plants
directions: Mix all ingredients and spray plants.
Be sure to spray under leaves.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Beat eggs and oil. Add all other ingredients and mix together. Put in slightly greased 10-inch glass pie pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Knife should come out clean when cutting.

title: crabmeat au gratin
directions: In a pan heat milk, chicken base, white pepper and Worcestershire to a simmer.
Do not boil.
In a pan melt butter; stir flour in and cook, stirring 2 minutes until flour is incorporated.
Stir in warm milk and cook, stirring until sauce is thickened.
Place crabmeat in a shallow 1 1/2 or 2-quart buttered casserole and sprinkle first with lemon juice, then with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with white sauce.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar over the top.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes until heated through and bubbly.
You may substitute crawfish tails for the crabmeat.
Makes 6 servings.

title: divinity candies
directions: May add pecan pieces, if desired.

title: mini cheesecakes(club member: terah smith)
directions: With hand mixer, beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla until smooth. Put cupcake liners in cupcake pan.
Put a vanilla wafer in each, flat side down. Put 1 tablespoon cream cheese mixture in each. Bake 15 minutes at 375°. Do not overbake or cakes will dry out. Cool cakes.
Remove from paper cups and top with 1 teaspoon pie filling.
Top with whipped cream. Keep refrigerated. Makes 24.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef in a soup pot; drain. Add all other ingredients and bring to a simmer. With lid on, simmer for 4 hours. Serve with sour cream and cheese.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Beat eggs until light. Add mashed bananas and add lemon juice. Blend with creamed mixture. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Mix into banana mixture. Add nuts. Bake in greased loaf pan at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: ultimate rocky road
directions: Melt over hot (not boiling) water the chocolate morsels; stir until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, nuts and sunflower seeds.
Spread in foil-lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix hash browns and oleo.
Add salt, pepper, soup, cheese, sour cream and onions.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: light salad
directions: Mix together and put in small baking dish.
Refrigerate several hours.
Cut into squares.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil the potatoes
until tender. Cool and grate.
Saute the onion and add
with
all
other
ingredients to the grated potato. Season to taste.
Top
with crushed corn flakes. Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: easy fudge
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients in a pan over low heat.
Let boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add the remaining ingredients.
Stir until melted.
Pour into a greased pan and let cool.

title: salami
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Take out and mix well again and return to refrigerator for another 24 hours.
Shape into loaves and bake on broiler pan at 160° for 8 hours, turning after first 4 hours.
After it cools, you can slice it and freeze it in sealed bags.

title: cheese cake
directions: Bake 55 minutes at 350°.

title: baked beans(fat-free)
directions: Soak beans overnight or use quick cook method on package. Drain off 1/2 the water after cooking.
Add remaining ingredients to cooked beans.
Put in a casserole dish and cover to bake.
Bake for 3 hours at 350°.
Let stand covered for 30 minutes before serving (to thicken sauce).
Serves 8 to 10.

title: dainty ham biscuits
directions: Slice rolls in half; spread half of mixture on each side. Layer ham, beef and cheese.
Spread a little of mixture on top. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: saucy stroganoff(low-fat)
directions: In a nonstick skillet, spray nonfat cooking spray generously. Saute beef or turkey, onion, mushrooms, garlic powder and dry mustard over medium-high heat until meat is browned and onion is tender.
Combine mayonnaise, yogurt and beef broth and add to beef mixture.
Cook over low heat 15 minutes.
Serve over hot noodles. Serves 4.

title: peanut puffs
directions: Cream shortening with peanut butter and salt until light and fluffy, gradually adding confectioners sugar.
Blend in vanilla, then flour.
Stir in peanuts; mix well.
Shape dough into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Roll immediately in confectioners sugar.

title: baked ham with cornbread-apricot stuffing
directions: Place ham on rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Slice to serve.

title: three week coleslaw
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well.
Place the remaining ingredients in saucepan and heat to rolling boil.
Mix cabbage and dressing.
Add 1/2 cup red wine vinegar.
Marinate three days in refrigerator before eating.
Keep in refrigerator in airtight container up to 3 weeks.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Bake at
for 20 minutes.	Grease cookie sheet and lay in wax paper.
Mix eggs, sugar, pumpkin, flour, spice and nuts in a bowl.
Stir
and pour in pan and bake.
Place a tea towel on counter
top
and sift powdered sugar on towel until its very white.
When
pumpkin
bread is done, place on towel and roll
up while
it's
very warm.
Let set.
Roll up until cold.
Unroll. Spread cream cheese filling and roll up again. Slice and enjoy.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Sprinkle vanilla wafer crumbs evenly in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Set aside.

title: waffles
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat egg yolks with fork.
Beat in milk and cooking oil.
In a large bowl, stir together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add egg mixture to flour mixture all at once.
Stir mixture until blended, but still slightly lumpy.
In small mixer bowl, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Carefully fold egg whites into egg-flour mixture.
Leave a few fluffs of egg whites.
Do not overmix.
Lightly grease waffle maker.
Cook; do not lift lid while baking.
Makes 3 or 4 (9-inch) waffles.

title: pizza on a cracker
directions: Place 12 crackers on uncoated paper plate.
Spread 1/2 teaspoon tomato paste on each cracker.
Top each with 1 slice pepperoni, 1 teaspoon shredded cheese and sprinkle with basil.

title: melissa's blue ribbon brownies(state fair blue ribbon winning recipe)
directions: In small saucepan, slowly melt margarine and chocolate.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Add salt.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Combine chocolate mixture and sugar, then fold in flour and chopped nuts, if desired.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla in medium saucepan and cook over medium-high heat until it comes to a full boil; stir constantly. Continue to stir and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla. Set aside to cool.
Make 2 pie shells and bake them.

title: carnival lemonade
directions: If you use 6 ounces lemonade concentrate, you use 4 cans of water.

title: green jello salad
directions: Mix jello and water together first, then add all ingredients. Chill.

title: chocolate chip cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese, butter and vanilla until fluffy. Gradually add sugars and beat until just combined.
Stir in chips. Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Place mixture on plastic wrap and shape into a ball.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Just before serving, roll in pecans.
Serve with graham crackers.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Eggs, sour cream and butter should be at room temperature.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add water to juice to make 2 1/4 cups.
Saute onion in shortening in large skillet until tender.
Add 1 1/4 cups water, carrots and bouillon.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and ginger.
Add catsup, vinegar and soy sauce and stir into vegetable mixture. Cook until clear and thickened.
Add chicken, green peppers and pineapple.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.

title: creamed onions
directions: Coarsely chop onions.
Boil onions in salted water.
Add butter to liquid; stir until melted.
Add white sauce to onion mixture.
Serve hot.
Serves 8 people.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump pineapple and cherries into pan and jiggle around to mix.
Sprinkle cake mix over fruit. Crumble margarine and nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until crunchy.

title: bruschetta al pomodoro
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place bread slices on baking sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden on each side.
Rub one side of the toasted bread with garlic and drizzle with a little oil. Arrange a few slices of tomato over each slice of bread.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with basil.
Drizzle tomatoes with more oil.
Serve while warm.
Serves 8.

title: cheese soup
directions: Saute until soft in the margarine the celery, onion and carrots. Add broth and milk, reserving 1/2 cup milk.
Combine flour and cornstarch in a bowl. Stir milk. Add soda and cheese last. Cook over low heat until cheese melts, stirring constantly. Serves 6 to 8.

title: texas enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add beans; mix well. Place 6 tortillas in casserole pan.
Layer ground beef mix, cheese and remaining tortillas in casserole.
Mix soup and Ro-Tel in bowl.
Pour over tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients, mix well.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaf. Makes 8 servings.

title: pumpkin pie(custard type)
directions: Beat all ingredients together until smooth.
Pour into two 9-inch unbaked pie shells and bake in a 425° oven for 45 to 55 minutes until silver knife comes out clean.
May look soft but will set later.

title: butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients to make a dough.
Use a cookie press to make different cookies (stars, bells, etc.).
Sprinkle colored candy sprinkles on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: dark brown chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Mix flour, soda and cocoa.
Add to sugar and oil alternately with buttermilk.
Heat coffee to a boil and add to mixture last.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Butter a small casserole dish and put in drained green beans. Slice hard-boiled eggs on top.
Pour a mixture of mushroom soup and milk that has been heated.
Place in 325° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: cheese-zucchini bake
directions: Mix cottage cheese, herbs, olives, egg and 1 tablespoon of the flour; set aside.

title: peach jello salad
directions: Mix jello, sugar and pineapple.
Cook 5 minutes.
Cool.
Whip cream cheese (softened) and 1 cup cold water together.
Add pineapple.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Mix Cool Whip in.
Pat in molds and refrigerate.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown beef and drain off excess fat.
Add sauce and water; simmer about 10 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients, except noodles, for filling.
Pour about one cup of sauce on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: lavon's cheese soup
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and cook 10 to 15 minutes, covered.
Do not drain.
Combine the next 3 ingredients and cook for sauce.
Add broth and cheese.
Combine all and heat until really hot, stirring to prevent scorching.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cube eggplant; cook until tender.
While eggplant is cooking, saute onion, bell pepper and celery in oleo.
Mash eggplant, leaving water in the eggplant.
Add crumbled cornbread and egg to mixture.
Add onion, celery and bell pepper.
Place in greased casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: While mixing eggs, sugar, salt, baking powder and flour together, heat milk and butter until near boiling point.
Add heated milk to mixture; beat for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla last. Bake in 350° oven for 28 minutes or until cake leaves the side of pan.
Will make 2 layer (9-inch) or sheet cake.
Use 7-Minute Frosting or fudge icing on this cake.

title: cheese puff
directions: In greased 6-cup souffle dish, combine Ritz crackers, cheese and mushrooms.
In medium bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, beat together eggs, milk, onion powder, parsley and poultry seasoning.
Pour over mixture in souffle dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until puffed and lightly browned.
Serve hot.

title: occidental hotel hot fudge
directions: Mix dry ingredients in medium saucepan.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Keep refrigerated.
May be reheated or serve cold.

title: coconut caramel dessert
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; press into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool completely.
Melt 1/4 cup margarine. Add coconut and 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Cook over low heat, stirring often until coconut is golden brown.
Cool.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Pour scalded milk over shortening, sugar and salt.
When cool, add 2 cups flour; beat well.
Add eggs.
Beat.
Add yeast which has been dissolved in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add rest of flour to make stiff mixture.
Let rise until doubled.
Melt 1/2 cup oleo, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1 tablespoon corn syrup.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle on nuts.
Roll dough until 1/4-inch thick. Spread with butter, 1/4 cup brown sugar and sprinkle cinnamon on. Roll like jelly roll.
Cut in 1-inch slices.
Let rise 1 hour. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Turn upside-down on foil.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Makes 2 pans of rolls.

title: funnel bread
directions: You will need 1 pie plate (bottom cut away).

title: congress tarts
directions: Make pie crust.
Either your own or pie crust mix.
Cut pie crust with cutter and line muffin tins.
Put teaspoon of jam on pie crust and then large tablespoon of batter mix on top.
Bake until golden brown at 300° to 350°.

title: red lentil chili
directions: Wash lentils.
Drain.
Cover with vinegar and tomato juice. Let soak for 2 hours.
Brown beef cubes and chopped onion.
Add spices; add to lentils and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours, adding hot water as necessary.
Freshness and quality of the spices makes a lot of difference, so check the flavor and correct the seasoning 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: apple crisp
directions: Wash apples; peel very thin.
Core, slice and place in shallow baking dish.
Mix together white sugar, spices and 1/4 teaspoon salt; sprinkle this and lemon juice over apples.
Blend flour, brown sugar, dash of salt and margarine until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples; pat down gently with back of spoon.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Store in tightly covered container.
To serve, dissolve 1 tablespoon of mixture in cup of hot water.
Yields 8 cups.

title: coconut pie
directions: Heat milk on stove. Add to hot milk the sugar, flour and salt (stir these together before adding to milk). Stir constantly and let boil on medium heat. Separate the eggs; beat egg yolks with fork until foamy. Stir eggs in fast when batter is ready. Put back on heat and stir constantly until it boils. Take off heat. Add vanilla, 1 tablespoon of butter and coconut.

title: oatmeal brownies
directions: In a bowl, combine the first seven ingredients; mix well, set aside 1 c for topping.
Pat the remaining mixture into a greased 15x10x1 baking pan.
Prepare brownie batter according to package directions.
Spread over the crust.
Sprinkle with the reserved oat mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool on a wire rack.
Cut into bars.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: stew(leprechaun stew)
directions: Heat oil in a 4-quart heavy, covered kettle.
Add lamb and garlic; cook until meat is browned.
Add boiling water; cover and simmer for 3 minutes.
Add carrots, celery, onion, potatoes, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer until all is tender.
Mix flour and cold water into a smooth paste.
Stir into hot stew. Keep stirring until thickened.
Serve with a garnish of chopped parsley.
Stew tastes better next day or two days later.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: In a bowl, combine all the ingredients.
Serve with beef.

title: olive corn pie
directions: Mix crumbs with melted butter.
Reserve 1 cup; press remainder onto bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Set aside.

title: cape cod clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and cut small.
Remove from pan.
Fry pork until golden brown.
Remove from pan.
Saute onions until soft.
Drain clams, saving juice, then chop clams fine.
Add to clam juice enough water to make 3 cups.
Bring to a boil and add potatoes, browned pork, onions and bacon.
Simmer until potatoes are done, about 15 minutes.
Blend flour to a smooth paste with cold water, add to the potatoes, stirring until it boils and thickens.
Add clams and seasonings.
Add the milk and add slowly to hot clam mixture.
Add 2 tablespoons butter when done.
Serves 6.

title: drop doughnuts
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon into hot lard until brown.

title: chess pie no. 1
directions: Combine
butter, sugar and vinegar in a saucepan.
Stir constantly
over
low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Pour hot mixture over beaten eggs, beating constantly.
Fold in vanilla and salt.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tomato basil linguine
directions: In a large serving bowl, combine the first seven ingredients. Let stand at room temperature for up to 1 1/2 hours.
Cook linguine according to package directions; drain.
Toss with cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: clam dip
directions: Stir all ingredients. Serve with crackers or chips.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Boil vinegar, sugar and water.
Mix together cornstarch, brown sugar and pineapple juice.
Add to liquid, cook until thickens. Saute pepper, onions and chestnuts.
Add oranges, pineapple and chicken.
Pour thickened mixture over.
Cook rice as directed. Serve chicken over rice or Chinese noodles, if preferred.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and well beaten egg.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill for 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: date torte
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar slowly, while beating.
Fold in dates and nutmeats.
Bake in buttered cake pan for 60 minutes at 325°.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: schnitzel beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; take out of skillet and drain.
Add sugar and vinegar to bacon grease.
Cook until sugar is dissolved. Add green beans and bacon, crumbled.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add onion.

title: black forest cake (schwarz wald torte)
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl, stir until well mixed.
Add shortening, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat 3 minutes at low speed.

title: lemon glazed persimmon bars
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and oil; mix well.
Stir 1 1/2 teaspoons lemon juice and baking soda into pulp.
Combine flour, salt and spices.
Add to egg mixture alternately with persimmon mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in walnuts and raisins. Spread in greased and floured oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool for 5 minutes.

title: "uptown" beer meat balls
directions: Combine first five ingredients and mix well.
Make small size (1-inch diameter) meat balls and fry in small amount of oil (if necessary) evenly on all sides.
Drain on paper towel.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer each ingredient, beginning with the lettuce.

title: meat filled jumbo shells
directions: Cook jumbo shells according to package directions; drain.
Cool on paper.
Brown beef and pork in skillet; drain.
Combine meat, eggs, bread crumbs, Mozzarella cheese (if desired), onion, oregano, salt and pepper.
Fill each shell with 2 tablespoons.
Spread a thin layer of sauce on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Place shells open side down, in a single layer in the pan; cover with sauce.
Cover with aluminum foil; bake at 350° about 45 minutes. Fills 36 shells.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: cherry congealed salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cottage cheese and crushed pineapple.
Add pecans and chopped cherries (save some for garnish). Add dry jello. Stir well. Chill.

title: j.g.'s macaroni and cheese
directions: Will need a 2 quart casserole dish.

title: italian sausage and cabbage
directions: Put sausage in large pot.
Cover with water at least 1 inch over top of sausage.
Boil about 30 minutes.
Remove sausage from broth; put into a bowl and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours or overnight. Strain through a tea strainer to remove all of the fat.
Put broth in pot.
Add cabbage, cut into wedges.
Place sausage on top and cook until done.
Season to taste.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until they form peaks. Add sugar gradually to the egg mixture. Continue to beat until mixture is very stiff. Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into gallon freezer and freeze as directed by ice cream maker.

title: edith's chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until it comes off the bone easily.
Cool and debone.
Put pieces into baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Pour cream of chicken soup and broth over chicken.
At this point, you can put into refrigerator or freezer.
Mix flour, buttermilk and oleo; pour over chicken mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: dorito delight
directions: Brown ground beef.
Once beef is brown, mix all other ingredients in a skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Cover the bottom of a casserole dish with the Doritos.
Pour in other ingredients.
Top with the Cheddar cheese.
Put in oven at 350° until cheese melts. If you wish, you may top with salsa and sour cream.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: hidden valley ranch buffalo wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken in mixture and melted butter, pepper sauce and vinegar.
Put in baking pan.
Sprinkle with 1 package dry dressing mix.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until browned.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with celery sticks and prepared Hidden Valley Ranch dressing as dip.

title: chile con queso
directions: Cut cheese into pieces. Chop the peeled chiles and the peeled tomato; add the other ingredients. Cook in the top of a double boiler, stirring occasionally. Serve hot with Fritos, tostados or crackers. This mixture should cook or rather melt down, about 3 hours. If possible, serve in a chafing dish or in some utensil over hot water.

title: watergate salad
directions: Fold each of the ingredients into the Cool Whip.
Cool to enhance the flavor.
Maraschino cherries placed on the top add a festive touch at Christmas.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix onions and salmon.
Let stand for 30 minutes, then add other ingredients.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: fast fixin' chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour oil into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Tilt pan until bottom is covered with oil.
Put remaining ingredients into pan; stir with a fork or spoon until blended (about 2 minutes).
Scrape sides and spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cooled cake may be sprinkled with powdered sugar. Use a knife to loosen cake from sides, cut and serve directly from pan.
Store leftover cake, loosely covered.

title: world famous meat loaf
directions: Beat thoroughly.
Put into loaf pan.
Cover with 2 strips bacon, if you like that flavor.
Pour over all one 8 ounce can Hunt's tomato sauce.
Bake one hour at 350°.
Serves six.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Parboil broccoli.
Place chicken breasts on top of broccoli in casserole dish.
Add cream of chicken soup and mayonnaise.
Mix and pour on top of chicken.
Add Cheddar cheese and bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: festive pumpkin or sweet potato bread
directions: Sift first 9 ingredients together.
Cream the sugar and oil in a large bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

Blend 1/3 cup water and pumpkin or sweet potato in bowl. Add pumpkin or sweet potato mixture alternately with dry ingredients to sugar mixture, blending well after each addition. Stir in raisins and nuts. Pour into 2 small greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bread tests done.

title: pickled shrimp
directions: Boil the shrimp in their shells with the celery leaves, pickling spices and 1 tablespoon salt for 5 minutes.
Drain shrimp and clean.
Place shrimp in covered container with a mixture made from the remaining ingredients for 24 hours.
Serve on toothpicks with pineapple cubes, green peppers and cheese cubes.

title: bountiful cream of broccoli cheese and clam bisque
directions: Microwave broccoli, onions, broth and salt, covered, 20 minutes.
Put aside 6 cooked broccoli flowerets for garnish. Puree broth mixture in food processor for a count of 20 seconds. Uncover.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cut orange slices into small pieces.
Use 1/2 cup of your flour to keep your knife clean.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat until very light.
Sift flour, salt and soda; add alternately with the coconut and nuts.
Add orange candy to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Drop by small teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes, or until light brown, at 350°.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in tightly covered container.

title: captain's choice easy holiday cheese ball
directions: In food processor or blender, finely chop beef and onions, then pour into mixing bowl and add cream cheese.
Shape into ball. Serve with crackers!

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add margarine, milk, vanilla and salt.
Mix well and pour in pie crust.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool before cutting.

title: three pepper pasta
directions: Saute ingredients in pan.
Be generous with lime juice.
Put over any kind of pasta (linguini or angel hair pasta).

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Place chopped green pepper, onion and pineapple on paper towel to absorb liquid.
Blend ingredients well.
Refrigerate and chill at least 1/2 hour.
Shape into ball.
Roll in chopped pecans, if desired.

title: glazed candied sweet potatoes
directions: Wash sweet potatoes, cover with water and partially cook until just tender enough to be pierced with a fork.
Do not over cook. Drain well and set aside.
Combine the oil or butter, brown sugar and juice and rind in a small saucepan.
Heat to boiling and cook for 2 minutes.
Peel the sweet potatoes and cut them in half lengthwise.
Place sweet potatoes in a shallow 8 inch square pan. Pour syrup over them.
Bake in a slow oven 300° for 55 minutes or until well glazed.
After the fist 15 minutes turn the potatoes and baste.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cut first 3 ingredients like pie meal. Take out 1 cup and reserve. Mix in other ingredients. Batter will be lumpy.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan. Top with remaining 1 cup. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: crunchy strawberry dessert
directions: Combine sugar and margarine; pour over pretzels.
Mix and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 9 minutes.
Cool.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Sift together baking powder, flour and salt.
Beat 2 egg whites until mounds form.
Set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar. Add 2 egg yolks.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with 1/3 cup milk.
Fold in egg whites; add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Add blueberries.
Bake in greased small tube pan at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle top with granulated sugar.
This cake is light and moist.

title: quick and easy brownies
directions: Melt margarine in microwave.
Mix in cake mix and egg (will be stiff).
Add chocolate bits.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan (not greased).
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
(Take from oven while still soft.)

title: phyl's famous egg rolls
directions: Saute pork and onions.
Add celery, cabbage and salt.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain.
Add bean sprouts.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes. Drain.
Fill wrappers as directed on package.
Deep-fry, may cook in wok or deep skillet (peanut oil works best).

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw
spinach.	Drain.	Chop
spinach
fine and fold in other ingredients.
Cut
off
slice from top of a 1-pound loaf Hawaiian bread.
Hollow
out
center, leaving a 1-inch shell. Break or
cut removed
bread into pieces.
Put dip into bread shell.
Use bread pieces to dip.

title: frozen coconut pound cake
directions: Cream
butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with sour cream.
Add vanilla and fold in
coconut.
Pour
into
large greased and floured tube pan. Using table knife, make 8 or 9 circles around, extending knife about 2 inches in batter.
Bake in a 300° oven approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: low-fat pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine prunes and water in container of food processor; pulse on and off until prunes are finely chopped.
In mixer bowl, blend prune mixture with sugars.
Beat in egg substitute and pumpkin just to blend.

title: twentieth century pound cake
directions: Cream well the Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Add milk and flour alternately. Add flavoring. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour in tube pan.
If desired, this can be used for cupcakes or layers.
Adjust time accordingly.

title: congealed strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Add banana, strawberries and pineapple.
Pour half in dish and let chill until partially congealed.
Cover with sour cream.
Top with remaining half mixture.
If desired, use 4 ounces sour cream and 4 ounces cream cheese.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen speared broccoli (10 minutes).
Spread broccoli on bottom of container.
Slightly beat eggs.
Shred cheese.
Do not dilute soup.
Mix the 5 ingredients and pour over the broccoli. Cover with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350°
for 50 minutes or until bubbly.

title: rich dinner rolls
directions: Mix milk, sugar, salt and butter; stir until sugar dissolves. Cool to lukewarm.
Pour warm water into a large warm bowl. Sprinkle in yeast and stir until dissolved.

Stir in milk mixture, eggs and 2 cups flour, beating with a wooden spoon until smooth. Mix in enough flour a little at a time to make a soft dough. Knead on lightly floured board until smooth and elastic.
Shape into ball and place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in a warm spot until double in bulk.
Punch down.
Roll out and form rolls. Let stand, covered, for 1/2 hour.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: parmesan bread
directions: Mix yeast with warm water and gently stir to dissolve completely.
Add cooled margarine, sugar, salt, egg, bran and Parmesan cheese.
Blend well.
Mix in flour.
Cover and let stand in a warm place about 2 hours or until doubled.
Punch down and turn out onto lightly floured board.
Knead just enough to form a smooth ball.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet (or any pan you like).
Cover and let rise about 40 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a dark golden brown.
Serve hot or cold.

title: nutty snickers pie
directions: Finely chop Snickers bars.
Mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar; fold in remaining ingredients and pour into crusts.
Keep refrigerated until served.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: tomato basil soup
directions: Saute the onions and garlic in the olive oil in a saucepan until transparent.
Stir in the tomatoes, stock, dried herbs, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Puree in small batches in a blender and return to saucepan.
Use caution when pureeing hot soup.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in the cream, fresh basil and fresh parsley.
Divide the rice between 6 soup bowls and ladle the soup over the rice.
Garnish with additional chopped fresh basil or parsley leaves.
Serves 6.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 1-quart casserole dish.
In 2-quart saucepan, melt butter or margarine.
Stir in flour, sugar and salt until blended.
Slowly stir in milk and cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in corn and eggs.
Pour into casserole dish and bake 1 hour or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, milk and cocoa in saucepan.
Boil for 3 minutes exactly.
Remove from heat and quickly add the remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
Let set for 30 minutes.
Makes 40 to 50 small cookies.

title: instant spice tea
directions: Stir and store in covered container.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown the hamburger; add the taco mix and onions and mix as directed.
Put in layers in cake pan:
cooked rice, chili beans, cheese, hamburger mixture and crushed Doritos chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
When serving, top with lettuce, tomatoes and taco or cheese sauce.

title: "lazy man" peach cobbler
directions: In large casserole dish put butter and melt in oven.
Mix in another bowl, flour, sugar, milk and peaches (with juice).
Add this to the butter in dish.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all items.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° or slower until done.
For a candied type pie, stir carefully every 10 or so minutes.
This keeps the pecans evenly distributed.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese and taco seasoning in baking dish.
Pour chili on top.
Layer with cheese.
Top with olives.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: lite broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add beaten egg, cottage cheese and seasonings.
Pour into sprayed casserole, sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hello dolly
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 8 or 9-inch square pan for 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: 100 years old ice box(refrigerator cookies)
directions: Stir dry ingredients in a large bowl, including nuts.
Melt butter, cool before it comes in contact with eggs.
Beat the eggs a little by hand.
Add all the wet ingredients and stir together with a spoon.
Roll off about 4 or 5 sheets of wax paper.
spoon the mixture onto the paper and form into a roll about 1 1/2 inch diameter. Roll up in the paper and twist the ends.
Store in the refrigerator overnight or until the dough is hard.
Take out of the paper, place on a cutting board and cut into thin slices with a sharp knife.
Here is where the advantages of a sharp knife comes in, cutting through those nuts!
Place them on a nonstick cookie sheet.
They won't spread out very much.
Bake at 325° for about 8 to 10 minutes, depending on how hot your oven is and how brown you want the cookies.
Cool and store in an airtight container.
They keep very well.

title: chalmer's spinach squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put butter in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Melt in oven.
Remove.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Put milk, Velveeta cheese, chicken soup, mushroom soup and diced green peppers in large saucepan.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Brown beef and add onions.
Drain fat.
Add taco seasoning.
Spray a 9 x 13 x 12-inch pan with Pam.
Layer tortillas, meat and sauce alternately in pan.
Sprinkle top with Cheddar cheese.
Cover with foil and bake for 25 minutes at 375°.

title: cheesy hash
directions: Thaw frozen hash browns to a point where you can break them up easily in baking dish.
Melt all ingredients (except potatoes) and pour mixture over potatoes
in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish. Let stand 1 hour, then bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Combine.
Roll into walnut size balls in sugar.
Add 2 teaspoons of cinnamon to sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix flour, shortening and brown sugar.
Save 1 cup of crumbs for top.
Add soda to boiling water.
Add table syrup.
Mix with flour, shortening and sugar mixture.
Pour in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add onions, celery, green pepper and garlic.
Cook until onions are tender.
Remove from heat.
Add tomato sauce, water and seasoning and stir.
Return to heat and simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
May add additional water if needed.
Stir in shrimp and heat to boiling.
Cover and reduce heat to medium and cook 10 to 20 minutes or until shrimp are pink and tender.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: rocky road brownies
directions: Sift together in sifter the flour, sugar, salt and cocoa.
Melt in pan the margarine and Crisco.
When cool, add to sifted ingredients.
Add the eggs, one at a time or beat together and add a little at a time, vanilla and nuts.
Pour in greased baking sheet and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: spiced tea cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for colored fluted tube pan).
Using solid shortening, grease pan and flour (12-cup tube pan).
(Also grease if nonstick finish.)
In large bowl, blend first 8 ingredients; beat 2 minutes at highest speed.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool upright in pan 15 minutes; turn on serving plate.

title: okra-tomatoes
directions: Cook 4 slices bacon and take out of frying pan.
Cook 1 medium onion and green pepper and cook 2 cups sliced okra until half done.
Then add 4 medium sliced ripe tomatoes and crumble bacon in it and cook all of this until tomatoes and okra are tender.

title: doughnut muffins
directions: Cream shortening and 1 cup sugar.
Add egg; beat well.
Mix and sift flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Add alternately with milk to egg mixture.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full. Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pans at once and roll in melted butter, then in mixture of remaining 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Makes 12 medium or 18 small muffins.

title: cheese dip
directions: Beat the egg and milk together in a Corning Ware dish.
Mix cheeses with milk mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve with nacho chips or crackers.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients together until it strikes a boil, then boil 2 minutes.
Have powdered sugar sifted and remove from heat; stir in.
Add vanilla.
Beat until it gets thick enough to spread.
Makes enough for 3 layers of cake.

title: fettucine au gratin
directions: You can tell if fish is fresh if the gills are pink with fresh red blood.
Fish should not smell fishy and the eyes should be clear and firm, not cloudy.
The inside should be clean and the meat should be firm.

title: georgia's tea cakes
directions: Mix sugar, butter, eggs and other ingredients.
Chill well before rolling out; cut with cookie cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; bake in an oven that has been preheated to 450°. Let the cookies stay in the 450° oven for about 1 minute, then turn oven to 375° and bake for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Peel and thinly slice potatoes and onion.
Place on top of chicken and lightly salt.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk biscuits(a great complement to any meal)
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Cut in butter and mix together lightly.
Add buttermilk and mix just enough to blend together. Do not overmix.

title: easy wassail
directions: Stick cloves around middle of oranges about 1 inch apart, then several close together at stem and bottom ends.
Bake, uncovered, in shallow pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Combine Tang, water, cider and cinnamon sticks in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix 1/2 pint of peanut butter and 1 pint jar of marshmallow cream. Mix until blended. Set aside.

title: egg strata
directions: Saute sausage until brown; remove from skillet and drain. Place sausage in bottom of casserole.
In same skillet, melt oleo; lightly saute thawed hash browns.
Cover sausage with hash browns; sprinkle cheese on top.
Beat eggs; add milk and salt.
Pour over ingredients in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican stack ups
directions: Brown hamburger, drain; mix with taco seasoning as directed on package.
Heat refried beans on low in medium pan.
Microwave tortillas 3 to 4 minutes in package, turning once.
Place tortilla on plate.
Spread tablespoon of beans and tablespoon of meat on it. Add cheese, lettuce, tomatoes and onions.
Place second tortilla on top and repeat steps (beans, meat, cheese, lettuce, tomatoes and onions).
Serves 6.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice apples into bottom of baking dish.
Dissolve cinnamon in water and pour over apples.
Mix together the flour, sugar and butter until smooth and crumbly. Spread over apples and bake for 30 minutes.

title: dolores' crab soup
directions: To make beef broth:
Cook soup bone with plate beef in 6 cups water, about 1 hour.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with bread slices.
Spread cheese mix over bread.
Put on a layer of meat. Beat eggs, add milk and mix together.
Pour over meat; put another layer of bread on top.
Bake 1 hour at 325° until puffy and brown. Can be fixed at night and baked in the morning.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Put breasts in a greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Put 1 piece of cheese over each piece of breast.
Mix chicken soup with 3/4 can of water.
Put dressing over chicken and cheese, then pour soup over all.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: sponge cake (hot milk)
directions: Whip eggs and sugar together.
Heat milk and butter. Alternate adding 1/4 flour and baking powder with 1/4 milk into egg mixture on low speed on your mixer.
After all of the flour mixture has been added to the egg mixture add the vanilla.

title: corn pudding
directions: Separate eggs.
Mix first four ingredients and egg yolks. Beat egg whites and fold into corn mixture.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with 1 teaspoon sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot cheese bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch loaf pan.
Combine Bisquick, cheese and sugar in a large bowl. Combine other ingredients in a second bowl.
Mix well.
Stir in dry mixture and blend thoroughly.
Beat slightly to remove lumps.
Turn into pan and bake until golden, 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 14 to 17 servings.

title: mexican lasagna(low-fat)
directions: In large skillet brown turkey with onion and pepper.
Add tomatoes and taco seasoning.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
In bowl, combine cottage cheese, 4 ounces Cheddar cheese and eggs. Place 3 tortillas on bottom of a sprayed 9 x 13-inch or 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Spoon meat mixture evenly over tortillas.
Top with 3 tortillas then cheese mixture.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top of lasagna and continue baking, uncovered, for 5 minutes or until cheese melts. Garnish with tomatoes and lettuce.
May add taco sauce or sour cream, if desired.

title: chicken tarragon(basilla)
directions: *Add to broth for added flavor.

title: oatmeal scotch chippies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, and granulated sugar in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Beat in eggs.
Add peanut butter.
Beat until blended.

title: alice's spanish pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in vegetable oil.
Place in large casserole. Top with remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 2 hours or until tender.
This is a meal in itself.
Serve with tossed salad.

title: shrimp and smokies
directions: Thoroughly wash the shrimp in cold water.
Pour the beer in a large soup pot.
Add the kielbasa slices to the pot along with the bay leaves, coriander seed and salt and pepper.
Bring ingredients to a boil over high heat.
Lower the heat and simmer, uncovered, for about 10 minutes.
Add the shrimp to the pot and bring back to a boil.
Boil until shrimp are firm and pink, about one to two minutes.
Drain off the cooking liquid and discard the bay leaves. Serve the shrimp and sausage in separate bowls.
Shell shrimp before eating.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hot dutch potato salad
directions: Dice bacon and panfry.
Add chopped onion and green pepper. Cook 3 minutes.
Add vinegar, salt, pepper, sugar and beaten egg. Cook slightly.
Add cubed potatoes, grated carrot and diced, hard-cooked eggs.
Blend slightly and serve hot.

title: french bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast over water and honey.
Stir.
Slowly add flour and salt; beat with wooden spoon. Turn dough out on floured board and knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Place dough in lightly greased bowl. Cover and let rise 2 hours.
Sprinkle corn meal in well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sad pancakes
directions: Blend in mixer.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: little hot dogs
directions: Wrap each hot dog with 1/2 slice of bacon.
Secure with toothpick.
Place in crock-pot and cover with brown sugar.
Cook on low for 8 hours.

title: chopstick tuna
directions: Combine soup and water; add 1 cup of chow mein noodles, tuna, celery, nuts and onion.
Toss lightly.
Place in ungreased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle over with remaining noodles. Bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes or until heated through.
If you double recipe, bake in larger baking dish for 25 minutes.
Can be prepared ahead of time and refrigerated.

title: orange smoothie
directions: Place all ingredients in blender. Cover and blend until smooth. Serve immediately. Makes 4 servings.

title: amazing peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into balls the size of a large walnuts.
Flatten on lightly greased cookie sheet with a fork. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, until lightly browned, at 350°.
Remove from pan carefully to cool.

title: bourbon hot dogs
directions: Add all ingredients to crock-pot.
Cook on low until all flavors are blended and hot dogs are plump.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Add to mixture.
Chill for at least 1 hour in refrigerator.
Roll in a mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Cut into desired shapes.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield:
4 to 5 dozen.

title: stir-fried garden
directions: Melt butter in a large (10-inch or larger) skillet.
Add cabbage and spinach.
When this cooks down a little, add the rest of your vegetables, stir and fry until done, about 15 to 30 minutes.
Add garlic powder, salt and pepper while cooking.
You can use your own mixture of vegetables.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix butter, sugar and cream.
Bring to boil over medium heat. Continually stir and boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until well mixed. Pour in pan.
Put nuts on top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease a casserole dish.
Place bite size pieces of chicken on bottom.
Mix soups together.
Pour and spread on top of chicken. Spread prepared dressing on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: egg pie
directions: Beat together the eggs, sugar and butter.
Add vanilla, then milk.
Pour in pie shells and bake at 325° to 350° until firm.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan. Bring to boil and continue boiling 1 1/2 minutes after mixture has reached a full rolling boil. Remove from heat. Put the rest of the ingredients in the boiled mixture. Drop by tablespoon onto wax paper.

title: veggie bars
directions: Press rolls in large cookie sheet and bake as directed on package.
Mix cream cheese, Hidden Valley mix and sour cream together.
Spread over rolls when cooled.
Top with grated and chopped veggies.
Spread the grated cheese on top.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: cocoa cola cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cola and the marshmallows, in large bowl.
Blend well and beat 1 minute at medium speed of mixer.
Add cola; blend well and stir in marshmallows.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: easy pumpkin cake
directions: Blend first 8 ingredients; pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with cake mix; scatter nuts on top.
Pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and refrigerate; may be frozen.

title: american indian fry bread
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Stir in beaten egg.
Add water to make soft dough.
Round up on lightly floured surface.
Knead lightly.
Roll or pat out 1/2-inch thick.
Shape in forms of turtles, snakes, pretzels or just plain strips.
Slit centers.
Drop into hot oil in skillet.
Brown on both sides. Serve hot.
Good too with pinto beans, soup, or with maple syrup.

title: corn flakes candy
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and cream until it reaches the soft-ball stage. Stir in remaining ingredients. Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper and let cool.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown beef in oil.
Remove from dish.
Saute celery, onion, garlic and parsley.
Add beef to pot again.
Add beef cube, water, tomato sauce and spices.
Simmer about 3/4 hour.
Add vegetables. Cook until tender.
Simmer, covered, about 1/2 hour longer.
Add beer anytime after vegetables.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix all ingredients and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: herbed broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Combine broccoli and remaining ingredients.
Spoon into greased, shallow 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until set.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in bananas.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; stir into creamed mixture.
Mix in nuts, if desired.
Spoon into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool on rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: low-fat turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix ground turkey and oats.
Add in garlic salt.
When well mixed, place in loaf pan, reserving some of the turkey mixture. Form a ditch in the middle of the turkey loaf.
Place sliced tomatoes in the ditch.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle basil over top.
Take remaining turkey mixture and cover over tomatoes and cheese.
Bake for about 1 hour at 350°.
